parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The breakage of the plastic part connected to the accelerator pedal can cause the entire pedal to need replacement, potentially leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal breaks
the pedal becomes loose or detached
the pedal is unable to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power while driving can cause the vehicle to slow down unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power without warning
the engine continues to rev without forward movement
the vehicle goes into a drift due to sudden decrease in speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The engine races when the vehicle is stopped
the speedometer registers high speeds when the vehicle is stationary
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly without applying the gas pedal
the vehicle does not shift into lower gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls and dies when slowing down
resulting in loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission makes unusual noises
the transmission warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission fails without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission makes unusual noises
the transmission warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure without warning can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails without warning
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission makes unusual noises
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may not be able to stop or slow down in time. Additionally, the non-deployment of airbags can further increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The brakes do not respond or engage
the vehicle does not slow down or stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle is involved in an accident due to brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Bosch Fuel Distributor Sensor Plate Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Bosch fuel distributor sensor plate can cause the vehicle to stall, flood, creep, and lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
floods
creeps
loses all power
and will not accelerate over 20 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear speaker amplifier can cause a loss of audio functionality, which may be a distraction to the driver and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: No sound or poor sound quality from the rear speakers
the rear amplifier system is not working properly.
